ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ROYAL BEATS LOUISVILLE IN GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ADAM BENSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wende Brown, last season's Southern Section 4-A Division Player of the Year, 
had eight kills and three blocks Tuesday night to lead Royal High to a 15-7, 
15-5, 15-0 win over host Louisville in the girls' volleyball opener for both 
teams. 
</P>
<P>
Brown got help from Becky Campbell, who added six kills, and Jennifer Hamilton, 
who had five kills and six blocks. 
</P>
<P>
"We had a good match against (Louisville) because we played well together," 
Brown said. "We were comfortable with each other's hitting. We are coming 
together." 
</P>
<P>
Louisville player Torie Sumner agreed. 
</P>
<P>
"They looked like they had been playing together for a long time," Sumner said. 
"Our team was a lot smaller than they were and their blocking was a big 
strength in their defense." ADAM BENSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
