<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amplicon Inc.: The Santa Ana computer equipment leasing company posted net 
income of $5.6 million for fiscal 1990, up 8% from the $5.2 million reported a 
year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue for the year ended June 30 rose 15%, to $158.3 million from $137.9 
million. Fourth-quarter net income totaled $1.7 million, 21% higher than the 
$1.4 million recorded for the comparable quarter in fiscal 1989. Revenue was up 
67%, to $46.7 million from $28 million. 
</P>
<P>
Patrick E. Paddon, chairman and president, said, "We are pleased with the 
results achieved during fiscal 1990, particularly with the momentum 
demonstrated by our strong fourth-quarter results." 
</P>
</TEXT>
