<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOUSE IS ON FIRE? HERE COMES SWAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN ANTONIO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southwestern Bell Telephone customers who dial the non-emergency number in 
their new directories for the city police department will get the local fire 
department instead. 
</P>
<P>
And vice versa. 
</P>
<P>
"We made an error," phone company spokesman Marco Gilliam said. "We are 
considering mailing at no charge to all our customers a peel-off sticker to 
place over (the mistake)." 
</P>
<P>
Company officers still have not determined how the error was made. 
</P>
