VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
MAN GIVES NOTE TO TELLER, ROBS BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man robbed a Simi Valley bank of several thousand dollars Tuesday afternoon 
using a demand note and the threat of a weapon, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Fidelity Federal Bank, 5775 Los Angeles Ave., reported the robbery about 1:45 
p.m., Simi Valley Police Lt. Neal Rein said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the man is about 25 years old, 6 feet, 2 inches tall and has 
blond hair, said Gary Auer, a special agent with the FBI's Ventura division. 
KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
