<HEADLINE>
<P>
MATTINGLY IS ACTIVATED BY YANKEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Don Mattingly, sidelined since July 25 because of a stiff lower back, was 
activated by the New York Yankees Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Mattingly is hitting .245 this season in 343 at-bats with five home runs and 35 
runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
He has not hit a home run since May 20. Mattingly's last appearance was July 24 
at Texas. He was placed on the 21-day disabled list the next day. 
</P>
<P>
"I was sure I would be back -- that was never a question," Mattingly said 
before Tuesday night's game against the Rangers. "In fact, I thought I would be 
back before this, but it took more time than I expected to come around. "I have 
no goals. I'm not looking to do anything offensively or defensively very 
special. All I want to do is play and stay healthy and not experience any more 
pain." 
</P>
<P>
Mattingly did not play in the Yankees' 5-4 victory Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
MATTINGLY, DON 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
