<P>
KMEX TELEVISION'S GENERAL MANAGER RESIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN LIPPMAN , From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Univision Holdings Inc., the Hallmark Cards subsidiary that owns 
Spanish-language KMEX-TV in Los Angeles, said the station's general manager, 
Emilio Nicolas Jr., has resigned and been succeeded by Richard P. Ramirez. 
</P>
<P>
Ramirez joined KMEX-TV, Channel 34, in April as general sales manager from 
WHCT-TV in Hartford, Conn., where he was general manager and a partner. 
</P>
<P>
Although KMEX-TV has been doing well in ratings, station sources said 
management in New York had been increasingly concerned about costs, in 
particular losses associated with "L.A. Fiesta Broadway," a Cinco de Mayo 
street fair that the station sponsored and broadcast earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
Nicolas, whose father started what is believed to be the nation's first 
Spanish-language station in San Antonio, said he hoped to remain in the 
broadcasting field. JOHN LIPPMAN 
</P>
