<P>
PIANIST CARSON TO OPEN CSLB SEASON WITH LISZT PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opening the 1990-91 concert season at Cal State Long Beach, pianist Michael 
Carson will give a complete performance of Franz Liszt's nine-part "First Year: 
Switzerland" (1848-54), from the composer's "Years of Pilgrimage," on a faculty 
recital in University Theatre, Saturday at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The rest of Carson's program lists four pieces by Rachmaninoff and Prokofiev's 
Seventh Sonata. 
</P>
<P>
This performance will benefit the Cal State Long Beach opera program, of which 
Carson is director. 
</P>
<P>
Information: (213) 985-5526. 
</P>
