<TEXT>
<P>
RATFINK: Ed (Big Daddy) Roth, the hot rod designer, cartoonist and 
quintessential Southern Californian, blames the decision to tear down the 
Huntington Beach Pier for his move last year to Utah. 
</P>
<P>
"That was it," says the creator of the obese rodent, "Ratfink." "That was the 
final straw." Roth, who worked as a sign painter at Knott's Berry Farm in the 
1980s, says: "What's left in California is a bunch of kids who don't have 
anything to do, so they turn to drugs." James Granelli and Robert Stewart 
</P>
