<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
UNIVERSITY PLANS CONCERT BY STARLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fireworks and classical music will highlight Cal State Fullerton's free Concert 
Under the Stars on Friday at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
A 5:30 p.m. picnic featuring Mexican-style dinners will precede the seventh 
annual concert on the lawn of the campus Performing Arts Building. 
</P>
<P>
As part of the annual community event, the university's wind ensemble will 
perform light classical music under the direction of Mitchell Fennell, musical 
director for the event. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton's new president, Milton A. Gordon, will also announce the 
university's Volunteers of the Year award, given annually by the Coordinating 
Council of Support Groups. 
</P>
<P>
The music is free for those sitting on the lawn or bringing their own chairs. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets for reserved seats are $4 and can be had by calling (714) 773-3371. 
</P>
<P>
For those interested in dinner and a seat, tickets are $12.50 for adults, $9.50 
for children, available only by calling the number above. 
</P>
<P>
For more information about the concert and picnic, call (714) 773-2108. 
</P>
</TEXT>
