<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
RECYCLING PROGRAM DELAYED TILL JANUARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although city officials had hoped to begin a new recycling program this month, 
delays in permit hearings for a processing plant that will handle the refuse 
have pushed back the start date to the beginning of January. 
</P>
<P>
Under the program, approved earlier this year, all refuse from the city will be 
taken to a plant in Stanton, where recyclable materials will be separated from 
the garbage using magnetic and weight-sensitive machinery. 
</P>
<P>
The city's 10-year contract with CR Transfer Inc. guarantees that at least 25% 
of the garbage collected in the city will be recycled, without residents having 
to separate plastics, glass or newspapers out of their trash bins. 
</P>
<P>
Until the plant is ready to accept the city's refuse, Newport Beach will 
continue its curbside newspaper pickup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
