<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
EL TORO'S MARINES PLAN RUNWAYS RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Toro Marine Corps Air Station is accepting applications for its Sept. 30 Run 
of the Runways. 
</P>
<P>
The third annual event will have races of 5 and 10 kilometers, plus a 
half-marathon. 
</P>
<P>
The first event will start at 7:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Awards will be presented in each age division for first through third place, 
plus a wheelchair division. 
</P>
<P>
The registration fee is $12 until Sept. 21 and $15 after that. Registration 
will be held on race day from 6 to 7 a.m. Proceeds will go to station's morale, 
welfare and recreation division to benefit Marines and sailors. 
</P>
<P>
Entrants should make checks payable to MWR 0230. For entry forms or 
information, call the MWR office at (714) 726-2571. Information and 
applications can also be obtained in writing: MWR Dept. Bldg. 75, MCAS El Toro, 
Santa Ana, Calif. 92709. 
</P>
</TEXT>
