<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA UNIFIED HAS 2 TEACHERS OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two teachers from the Santa Ana Unified School District have been chosen as 
Orange County Teachers of the Year for 1990-91, Supt. Rudy Castruita announced 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
This is the first time in the history of the competition that two teachers from 
the same district have been selected by the Orange County Department of 
Education, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Dee Gomez, an English-as-a-second-language teacher at Santa Ana High School, 
and Lynn Maher, an English teacher at MacArthur Fundamental Intermediate 
School, were the winners, Castruita announced at a school board meeting. 
</P>
<P>
"I think it's a real feather in our teacher corps' caps," Castruita said. 
</P>
<P>
Gomez, who was in the audience, said she was "overwhelmed" by the honor. Being 
a good teacher means "total commitment," she said. 
</P>
<P>
"You can't look at a kid just when he's in your classroom. You also need to 
look at him when he's outside your classroom," she said. "It's the whole 
student." 
</P>
<P>
Gomez and Maher will now compete for California Teacher of the Year, which will 
be selected by the state Department of Education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
