<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHY DIDN'T BUSH FIRST GET CITIZENS OUT? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
First, before we start to cry over spilled milk, I would like to say I think we 
should have waited to follow the U.N. lead and not gone into Saudi Arabia like 
charging elephants. 
</P>
<P>
Now that we are there, how to get out and not lose one American or Arab boy to 
this debacle is our problem. 
</P>
<P>
Let's say to the U.N., "What do you want us to do?" and do it. 
</P>
<P>
Nothing wimpy about that. I think the whole world would breathe a sigh of 
relief and the lives of thousands would be saved. 
</P>
<P>
I am not taking a guilt trip from Secretary of State James Baker, who said, "We 
have to stay united." 
</P>
<P>
No one asked me if I wanted in and no one is asking me if I want out. I'm 
saying I want us out in our unilateral role and back the U.N. in any role they 
want us to take with the rest of the world. 
</P>
<P>
EILEEN MURPHY 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
