<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY VOLLEYBALL TOURNAMENT SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thirty-seven girls' volleyball teams will compete this weekend in the Orange 
County high school championships. 
</P>
<P>
The two-day, three-division tournament begins Friday, with the finals on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The finals of the Division I tournament, which is composed of the county's top 
10 teams, is scheduled for 6 p.m. at Edison High School. 
</P>
<P>
The Division II finals will be at 4 p.m. at Marina High and the Division III 
finals will be at 4 p.m. at Westminster High. 
</P>
<P>
Three Division I teams are ranked nationally by Volleyball Monthly magazine -- 
Corona del Mar (second), La Habra (11th) and Newport Harbor (12th). 
</P>
<P>
Today's Division I schedule (all games at Edison): Mater Dei vs. Edison, 3 
p.m.; Woodbridge vs. Fountain Valley, 3 p.m.; La Habra vs. Capistrano Valley, 5 
p.m.; El Toro vs. Newport Harbor, 5 p.m. Corona del Mar will play the winner of 
the Edison-Mater Dei game at 7 p.m., and Laguna Beach will play the winner of 
Woodbridge-Fountain Valley at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Division II and III teams will begin pool play at 8:30 a.m. Saturday at their 
respective sites. MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
