ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VTN's Net Doubles: VTN Corp., the Orange-based engineering, land-planning and 
consulting firm, said net income more than doubled for the fiscal year ended 
May 31, to $1.9 million from the $713,333 reported for the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
Sales declined 10%, to $11.1 million from $12.4 million for the previous year. 
Fourth-quarter figures were not available. Chairman Daniel C. Montano said the 
company's domestic land development engineering business is feeling the 
industry softness occurring across the country. 
