<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: INVESTORS GET BIG CHUNKS OF TOKOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two institutional investors -- Montgomery Medical Ventures L.P. of San 
Francisco and Allstate Insurance -- have attained substantial ownership 
positions in Tokos Medical Corp. as a result of Tokos' Aug. 31 acquisition of 
Physiologic Diagnostic Services. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana-based Tokos said Tuesday that Montgomery's 32% ownership of PDS has 
been converted into a 6.7% interest, or 968,800 of its shares, and Allstate's 
29% ownership of PDS has been converted into a 5.1% interest, or 742,000 
shares. 
</P>
<P>
Tokos provides monitoring devices and home-monitoring services to women with 
high-risk pregnancies. 
</P>
