<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Center for Contemporary Art will celebrate its 10th 
anniversary with an art auction and reception on Sept. 23 from 5 to 9 p.m. at 
the gallery, 3621 W. MacArthur Blvd. in Santa Ana. Maurice Hansen of Hansen 
Auctions, San Clemente, will knock down works donated by artists in Orange 
County and Los Angeles to benefit OCCCA. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets to the fund-raiser -- which includes pop and jazz entertainers and an 
hors d'oeuvres buffet -- are $30 ($15 of which is tax-deductible), and 
reservations are requested by Sept. 19. The art can be previewed at OCCCA on 
Sept. 21 and 22 from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. VISA and MasterCard will be accepted for 
art purchases. For more information, call (714) 549-4989 between 11 a.m. and 4 
p.m., Wednesday through Sunday. 
