</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SENECA, S.C. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Max Hedglin is anything but a wallflower when it comes to expressing his 
feelings. 
</P>
<P>
He hired a helicopter to drop 2,500 carnations and 10,000 love letters on the 
lawn of his former girlfriend. 
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately for Hedglin, 38, who owns a convenience store in nearby 
Greenville, the $3,000 tribute on Saturday failed to take root with Bonnie 
Adams. But then, a week earlier she had married City Councilman Mike Adams. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities charged Hedglin with littering. On Tuesday, he pulled up outside 
the Police Department in a stretch limo and paid a $237 bond. 
