<P>
MACLAINE TO TWINKLE TOES LESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shirley MacLaine's song and dance act will be a little less dance and a bit 
more song. 
</P>
<P>
She blames age. 
</P>
<P>
"It's real life that's a problem. I can't run for a cab in the rain in the 
streets of New York anymore," the 56-year-old MacLaine said. 
</P>
<P>
After 40 movies, five TV specials, six books and a half a century of dancing, 
MacLaine said on the new syndicated TV show "Personalities" that it was time to 
"scale down the dancing." 
</P>
<P>
"It isn't that direly necessary to me. At this stage, I think it's bombastic 
because of my age you can still do this stuff," she said in the interview 
broadcast Monday. 
</P>
