<TEXT>
<P>
Pierre Salinger has signed a new contract for three more years with ABC News. 
</P>
<P>
He will remain in London with the dual jobs of chief foreign correspondent and 
senior editor, Europe. 
</P>
<P>
Salinger, who was press secretary to President John F. Kennedy and served 
briefly as a U.S. senator from California, joined ABC News in 1977 and has 
spent most of his time in Paris and London for the network, winning a 
shelf-full of awards along the way. 
